01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:29.000
in one case.

01:03:29.000 --> 01:03:33.000
If the profitability of the business

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:37.000
is higher than the costs of this scheme,

01:03:37.000 --> 01:03:41.000
if the business is low-profitable,

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:45.000
then there is no point in resorting

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:49.000
to loans in a bank.

01:03:49.000 --> 01:03:53.000
You should work only with your own money.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:57.000
And it is even better if your business

01:03:57.000 --> 01:04:01.000
is high-profitable.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:05.000
If your business is high-profitable,

01:04:05.000 --> 01:04:09.000
everyone works with you with pleasure.

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:13.000
Banks, factoring companies,

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:17.000
and the next question we will consider

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:21.000
is the management of money assets.

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:25.000
The fact is that

01:04:25.000 --> 01:04:29.000
a part of the assets of any enterprise

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:33.000
is in the form of money.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:37.000
The money is in the account.

01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:41.000
On the one hand, these money

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:45.000
should be used to cover the costs

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:49.000
of the enterprise.

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:53.000
For this, you need money

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:57.000
to cover such costs every day.

01:04:57.000 --> 01:05:01.000
On the other hand,

01:05:01.000 --> 01:05:05.000
in the condition of inflation,

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:09.000
keeping an excessively large amount

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:13.000
of money in the account is not profitable

01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:17.000
for the business.

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:21.000
If there was no inflation,

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:25.000
then it would be a completely different story.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:29.000
But if there is inflation,

01:05:29.000 --> 01:05:33.000
it devalues money every day.

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:37.000
It is like a clock counting seconds.

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:41.000
It is like a clock counting seconds.

01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:45.000
If you have a lot of money in the account,

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:49.000
you lose a lot of money every second.

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:53.000
But if there is not enough money,

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:57.000
you cannot cover your current needs.

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:01.000
This leads to a failure of production.

01:06:01.000 --> 01:06:05.000
Imagine that you cannot buy supplies of raw materials.

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:09.000
Yes, you saved money, but you did not lose money on inflation.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:13.000
But your production stopped.

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:17.000
Again, there is a golden mean.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:21.000
There should not be too much money in the account,

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:25.000
but there should be exactly as much as is needed

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:29.000
to cover the current needs.

01:06:29.000 --> 01:06:33.000
So that you do not have daily problems

01:06:33.000 --> 01:06:37.000
in your business.

01:06:37.000 --> 01:06:41.000
What are the needs that need to be covered?

01:06:41.000 --> 01:06:45.000
Are all the needs that the enterprise has

01:06:45.000 --> 01:06:49.000
to be covered with money?

01:06:49.000 --> 01:06:53.000
No, only the primary needs,

01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:57.000
which cannot be covered even tomorrow.

01:06:57.000 --> 01:07:01.000
The needs that are more important than their repayment.

01:07:01.000 --> 01:07:05.000
These needs should be covered with money.

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:09.000
And this money should be in the account.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:13.000
If there is more money in the account,

01:07:13.000 --> 01:07:17.000
it means that they are not being used effectively.

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:21.000
They are being lost.

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:25.000
Even if there was no inflation,

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:29.000
we could also talk about the ineffective use of money.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:33.000
The money is being used in other forms of assets,

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:37.000
which bring additional income.

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:41.000
We should pay attention to this.

01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:45.000
At least the minimum deposit in the bank.

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:49.000
There is a deposit in the bank, there is additional income.

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:53.000
It's just that the money in the account

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:57.000
does not bring any additional income to the enterprise.

01:07:57.000 --> 01:08:01.000
The money in the account is the minimum sacrifice

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:05.000
that the enterprise has to make

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:09.000
in order to function properly.

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:13.000
To determine the minimum amount of money

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:17.000
that should be in the account,

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:21.000
we will use the formula presented on the slide.

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:25.000
The minimum amount of assets

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:29.000
for the enterprise is determined

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:33.000
as the ratio of the estimated amount of payment

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:37.000
for the current economic operations

01:08:37.000 --> 01:08:41.000
in the coming period according to the plan of income and expenses,

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:45.000
and the turnover of cash assets in the following period.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:49.000
Pay attention to the numerator.

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:53.000
The estimated amount of payment.

01:08:53.000 --> 01:08:57.000
For example, this year we plan

01:08:57.000 --> 01:09:01.000
to need this amount of money.

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:05.000
And in the denominator,

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:09.000
the turnover of cash assets in the same period in the past.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:13.000
That is, per year,

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:17.000
how many times cash assets

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:21.000
of this enterprise are turned around.

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:25.000
By dividing one into another,

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:29.000
we get the amount of money we need in the account.

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:33.000
The fact is that the assets that we have in the enterprise

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:37.000
are constantly turning around.

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:41.000
Remember, liquidity of assets, their ability to turn into cash.

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:45.000
So, the assets are constantly turning around,

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:49.000
from material form to cash form,

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:53.000
and the amount of money we need

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:57.000
should remain the same all the time,

01:09:57.000 --> 01:10:01.000
but not more than the amount required for the current needs.

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:05.000
And the current needs are determined

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:09.000
in terms of income and expenses.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:13.000
The important thing is that the plan is realistic,

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:17.000
that the amounts that must be paid

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:21.000
in the current period,

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:25.000
and that cannot wait until

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:29.000
additional money is turned into cash,

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:33.000
